    "body": "Hey! @mprakhov \r\nI hope I understand the issue correctly. What I did in the mobile for changing password flow when a user has biometrics activated: https://www.figma.com/file/vivAF5JmeyFBz1791nwD7r/Privacy-%26-Security?node-id=3764%3A201369&t=dTs02Gx1RPPrqXas-1\r\n\r\n\r\n(Don't be surprised about 2 fields on this screen instead of 3 I thought if biometrics is activated, and we know the current user password, there is no need to ask them to enter the current password) \r\n\r\nSo if a user wants to change their password, \r\nthey go to Settings --> create a new one -->, restart the app -->, log in again",
