    "body": "I have posted this in the `dogfooding` channel of Status Community, but just for reference pasting it here as well:\r\n\r\nThere are few cases where we need to pay attention:\r\n- `change password`\r\n  - `regular user`\r\nif password change went well (menas the db is re-encrypted using new pass) we just need to set `storeToKeychain` prop locally to `notNow` and display a popup to a user where the only option will be `Sign out & Quit` and that's the only thing user may do from that state. That further means on next app run, when user logs in using new password we offer him to store that new password to a keychain (that's something which is already in place).\r\n  - `keycard user`\r\nchange password should be disabled in this case\r\n- `enabled/disable biometrics` (so far a feature available only to mac users)\r\n  - `regular user`\r\nwhen user disables biometrics we just need to set `storeToKeychain` prop locally to `never`, when user enables it, we need to let user enter a current password, check it and if it's valid we need to store it to keychain and update `storeToKeychain` prop to store\r\n  - `keycard user`\r\nthis feature needs to be enabled only if user has migrated his profile keypair to a keycard, in that case when user disables biometrics we just need to set `storeToKeychain` prop locally to `never`, when user enables it we need to run appropriate flow and ask him for a keycard where his profile keypair is migrated to and once he enters a correct pin we need to store it to keychain and update `storeToKeychain` prop to `store`.",
